definitions.definition: That which results; the conclusion or end to which any course or condition of things leads, or which is obtained by any process or operation; consequence or effect.
examples: the result of a course of action;  the result of a mathematical operation

definitions.definition: The final product, beneficial or tangible effect (s) achieved by effort.
The decision or determination of a council or deliberative assembly; a resolve; a decree.
The final score in a game.
A positive or favourable outcome for someone.
